🌱 Eco-Friendly Concrete Strength Predictor

Predict the compressive strength of eco-friendly concrete using AI-powered models! This project leverages Deep Neural Networks (DNN), XGBoost, and CatBoost to provide accurate, sustainable, and reliable predictions.

🚀 Why This Project?

Concrete is the backbone of construction, but traditional concrete has a huge environmental footprint. 🌍
This project focuses on:

Sustainable, eco-friendly concrete solutions 🌿

Accurate strength predictions using AI & gradient boosting 🤖

Clean, reproducible, and interpretable modeling pipelines

🛠️ Features

✨ AI Models: DNN, XGBoost, CatBoost
✨ Data Cleaning: Outlier removal using IQR
✨ Feature Scaling: StandardScaler for normalized input
✨ Hyperparameter Tuning: RandomizedSearchCV for optimal performance
✨ Evaluation Metrics: MAE, R², A20 Index (±20% accuracy)
✨ Visualization: Scatter plots, loss curves, and performance summaries

🔍 Workflow

Load & Explore Data – Check structure, stats, missing values

Clean Data – Remove outliers for better predictions

Prepare Features – Scale features, split into train/val/test

Train Models – DNN, XGBoost, CatBoost

Tune Hyperparameters – Optimize models for best performance

Evaluate & Visualize – Compare predictions using metrics and plots

📊 Example Results
Model	MAE	R²	A20 Index
DNN	2.3	0.92	0.85
XGBoost	2.5	0.90	0.82
CatBoost	2.1	0.93	0.87

(Results may vary depending on dataset and training)

🖥️ Quick Start

Clone Repo:

git clone https://github.com/yourusername/eco-friendly-concrete-ai.git


Install Dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt


Run Notebook or Script:

Mount Google Drive if using Colab

Load dataset and execute cells to train and evaluate models

